<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000688/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Continuous evaluation system (Sistema de Evaluación Progresiva), with the following temptative weights and with a minimum proficiency requirement in each concept:

20% Class Attendance/Participation
20% Class Presentation based on readings
As part of the course work, students will carry out a work focused on health systems. To do this, they will document themselves regarding different possible public-private collaboration systems and will be in contact with the actors involved: the Ministry of Health in Madrid, Health Centers and Hospitals. Students must, from an international perspective, propose improvements to the menu of services for the Madrid health system. This work will represent 20% of the evaluation of the subject.
20% Book Review Group Project (written paper+presentation)
20% In-class Midterm Exam
20% In-class Final Exam

Sistema de Prueba de Evaluación Global:
Final Exam+required Written project"""@es ;
